content.detailedDescription:
1. i was  6 years old and the passenger of a car going to a dinner party with my mom, we were driving n/e towards california city ca about to drive over the trona train tracks. it was day light out still and very close to my 7th birthday.

2. as we hit the train tracks we were engulfed in a blinding white light, and a powerful roaring noise.

3. i thought i was going to die from being hit by a train was my first reaction, until i realized i wasn't dead but could see nothing but the white light everywhere and the roaring noise was so loud i blacked out as everything disappeared.

4. i never seen a object do to the initial contact being the white light and noise directly above us. the light was so bright. brighter then 50 suns. i could not see my mom or my hand in my face. the whole car and everything around me disappeared in a flash of light and noise. 

5. during the sighting i thought i was going to be ran over and killed until i knew i wasn't dead and blacked out. i woke and it was dark out and i was sitting in the passenger seat in my moms camaro and all the lights were blinking as well as the radio was going in and out. we were stopped on the other side of the tracks on the right side of the road. my mom was sitting in the drivers seat with a blank stare on her face with her eyes open and not moving. she remained like this for several minutes and then came too screaming and yelling. she grabbed me by my shirt and violently shook me screaming "are you alright?" over and over again. i responded i was ok, closed my car door and we drove off.

6. while i was blacked out, the object had already left the scene.
content.summary: Childhood ufo abduction with parent involving moving car

content.detailedDescription: While walking on a gravel road called ''bentley''in washington state, i came across two separate conical impressions in the road to the left of fallow wheat field. on an almost daily basis during the summer i walk to a weather tower and back again to my vehicle. i noticed these impressions while on my return walk from the weather tower and after seeing the first one,then back-tracked and found the other impression about 45ft. in a nearly straight line from the first. each was about 1/4th of an inch deep. i noticed a powdery-looking residue that seemed to be from the lighter crushed gravel, the heavier gravel being pushed underneath.No one seems to know what made them. my uncle took me back out to the area a week later so i could show them to him,but they had either been ''graded'' out or run over by heavy farm vehicles.I have no idea what made them.
content.summary: While walking gravel road i found two seperate round impressions in road next to fallow wheat field. each about 45 ft. apart in a nearly straight line from the other.

content.detailedDescription:

the sky was very clear at this time, i kept a little look at the sky until i caught a glimpse of something strange that i did not believe, i saw the light go up from somewhere on the ground vertically to the sky with remarkable speed and stop for a second to complete it's way.
at first i could not believe what i'm seeing i did not put it in the possibilities that was a military plane because the military airport away from my home 50 kilometers south of this ufo appeared from the west. there is no possibility that a civilian aircraft, the nearest civilian airport is located 200. plus i have checked the radar of civil aircraft program to make sure the situation and found that the nearest plane to me situated in the capital, which lies 200 kilometers from me and there was not on the scale of entire city any aircraft at this time.
the body was the closest thing to a cylindrical glossy white that i've never seen before, it was flying in a little zigzag movement can not be an ordinary plane to fly like that, and high speed i've never seen before, especially at this altitude.
i could not do anything i was impressed and shocked at the same time because i'm seeing something like this for the first time, i have camera attached to a mobile phone and the sky was dark and did not help me picking up the lighting for something clear as well that this was the body quickly. i went immediately afterwards to report on this website.
i could not follow it because it had gone to the other side of the building where i live.
i've attached a short video that i was able to catch, i no it's not very clear but if you focused you will catch that speed light.

content.detailedDescription:
Ufo over alexandria, va
11/10/15- veterans day
location of sighting: west on eisenhower ave
time: 4:25 pm
witness: les thomas

while traveling west on eisenhower ave. as passenger in the back seat of the car driven by robin b.  w/ her husband cabin on the passenger side. we were on our way to a local restaurant when i happened to look out the window on the driver side in the back when i just glanced up.  what i saw was several jets (i assumed) flying several miles over-head, saw their contrail which seemed normal in their shape. i was about to look away when a bright, shinning silvery object caught my eye. it was traveling southward towards ft. belvoir/ lorton area as far as i could tell. the object left its own contrail but it was different from those of a passenger jet. unlike the thick white exhaust that cones out from behind the jet, the object left a thin wispy trail that had a swirling/distroted effect, the object was circular-like, i could not tell its exact shape but it was not a jet, plane, blimp, balloon or kite. it gave off its own light and was not reflecting sunlight. i heard no sound because of the noise from the traffic, plus i had the window up. the object was moving slowly compared to the jets  higher up. we drove pass a row of trees that blocked out the object, i looked away for just a moment, looked back up and it was gone. i watched the skies for a few minutes more, but never saw it again. i told the others in the car what i saw, they did not see anything at all. the total time i viewed the object was about 3-5 minutes tops. i would like to known if anyone else saw anything weird in the skies of south fairfax county on veterans day? if so please respond. ps: i took pictures but, it was on a flip phone- if you ever try to take a pic of some super bright with one you know things can blur. the object can't be clearly seen because of the intensity of the objects glow. also remember, i'm in a moving car heading away from the object.
content.summary: Double tiered flatish silver/bright like electrical torch

content.detailedDescription:
It was the night of the peak of the august meteor shower. i was looking for meteors. as there were no meteors yet (it was too early for meteors, about 9.30) i watched a plane flying from n to s. then i noticed a big, green ball of light in the w. i thought it was a meteor at first. it wasn't. the light was unblinking and travelling straight from w to e, not falling. i watched as it moved, covering twice as much sky as the plane did in half the time. it never made a noise. by the time the plane and the object nearly met, i was extremely scared, expecting a collision. at the last moment, right before they intersected, the green ball of light stopped and shot straight up. it disappeared and the plane went on its way.

i've thought about it for the last few months. i'm a pretty skeptical person. i thought of 20 different ways to debunk it, but they never account for what happened. finally, i decided to report it.
content.summary: Big green light crossed the sky w to e. perpendicular to airplane. shot straight up when it nearly hit.

content.summary: 6 orange orbs floated across field and ascended into space

like i said, earlier that year, i had witnessed the exact same thing, only i was living in a different part of the state altogether. never would i imagined i would ever see something like it again...And so soon! 
after both occurrences, the object just floated off into the distance, almost flickering out, then reappearing for a second or two before disappearing for good.

content.detailedDescription: I was walking home from a friends after a night out at 7am, i saw a large bright object in the sky which appeared static and seemed to be refracting a large amount of light from an unknown source. i returned to my friends house to ask him to look at the object with me, he said it was probably the international space station and told me to forget about it. i made my way back home again and it hadn't moved by the time i got home. i opened my back door to film the object which still appeared stationary and large in the sky. as soon as i took the video i okayed it back but what i saw on the camera was completely different to what i could see in the sky. the large object appeared much smaller and was darting about in random directions very quickly. it seemed to change shape as it did so. it still appeared static when observed by the naked eye. around 45 minutes later it slowly flew out of sight.
content.summary: Large object refracting light in the sky appeared static, when filmed could be seen flitting about very quickly and changing shape

content.detailedDescription:
I was riding passenger traveling east on jack london blvd with my father and uncle. the sky was completely clear, the temps stayed in the upper 50s all day as we have been experiencing an artic chill, and i was just staring out the window as i often do from the passenger seat. i noticed what appeared to be a very short jet contrail at a high altitude that would disappear quickly and reappear in puffs or pulses as the object, which was very hard to see, seemed to be descending because the contrail was vertical, not horizontal as it would normally be. the contrail was far more visible to the naked eye, and i only saw a very brief split second reflection of light off a solid object at the front of the trail. i had never seen short bursts of contrail like that before and asked, "what is that?" 
my uncle, who was driving, asked what i was looking at, not being one to take his eyes off the road. i described it to him and he said it was probably a pulse jet. though i had never heard of a pulse jet, it seemed plausible and i left it at that. i continued to watch as disappear, never taking my eyes off it. considering the object was nearly invisible and most of all i witnessed was the trail, i assumed it was a jet descending and as it did, less contrail was visible until i could no longer see any thing. it really did just seem to vanish. the whole sighting lasted no longer than 3 min. how ever some research in to pulse jet engines revealed that there has been little to no success with using them for air craft, except in the hypothetical case of the aurora project. while i believe what i saw may have been some sort of jet, it seemed a tad bit mysterious and maybe worth reporting.
content.summary: Unknown object oberved giving off a short burst of contrail se of livermore

content.detailedDescription:
I was putting up christmas lights when i looked up into the corner of the house to plug in a new string.  when i looked up i was facing northeast, and was looking past the northwest corner of the house, i was on the west side of the house.  i saw what appeared to be an object on fire in the sky coming from the northeast.  the fact that it was not blinking, along with the color, which was more of a cross between amber street lights and fire, kept my interest.  i watched as it went almost directly over head, and then continued to visually follow it as it moved to the southwest.  it moved in a straight line.  i remember thinking that it had to be low, because it was under the clouds, and the size of the glow would further indicate that it was not high in altitude. if i were to hold a ruler at arms length to measure it, it would have been about an inch long.

  anything that low should be heard as well as seen, yet i heard no noise.  i was intrigued to say the least.  while it was moving overhead i was afraid that i would lose it as it passed over the tree in the front yard, so i moved across the yard, toward the south.  i kept visual contact with the object until it went through the clouds in the south southwest section of the sky.  

i love and study aircraft of all kind, and i have never seen an aircraft with a light that was this color.  that told me that something was not right.  as far as what i am feeling after seeing this....It was nearly 2 hours ago, and i still have goosebumps when i think about it.  i have been watching the skies to see if i can see another one, but no luck.
content.summary: Saw an object that was beneath clouds, yet heard no sound from it.

content.detailedDescription:
Observed from rosemount mn @ chippendale & carousel (zip 55968), appeared to be over apple valley to the west

first noticed because it was so bright and appeared solid and short - not like a long fluffy contrail

i thought maybe it was a meteor but i kept watching it and it wasn't moving fast like a typical meteor shower

i turned onto county road 46 and headed west so it was directly in front of me.  it seemed to become more silvery as the sun was going down.   it seemed to be descending but quite slowly and not by much.  when i reached the major intersection of 46 & pilot knob it was behind a sign - this was approximately 4 minutes later (4:49pm ct).  i turned south on pilot knob hoping to reach my mother's home and use her telescope but i lost sight of it in the trees while driving.
content.summary: Reflective object over minnesota
